history.content: If you have the prereqs, definitely go for 140 if you're choosing between the two. 134 only has weekly homework assignments and 140 has written homework and computational labs, which might result in a slightly higher workload, but the course staff and Prof. Adhikari do a great job helping you understand the material. When I took it, I felt like I did not need to spend as much time outside of lecture and discussion to understand concepts as I usually did in other classes so I could jump directly into the assignments. So overall 140 should not be significantly more work but a lot more worthwhile. I would be cautious of the other three classes that you already have on your schedule though, but if you're determined to take one of the two, take 140.
